            'Honour killing' video shocks Syrians
            The release of a brutal video showing a young Syrian women being murdered in a so-called "honour killing" has been met with horror online. Women's rights activist Rima Flihan describes how the war has made such killings increasingly common.Video produced by Lina Shaikhouni and Suniti SinghBBC Monitoring reports and analyses news from TV, radio, web and print media around the world. You can follow BBC Monitoring on Twitter and Facebook.
                
